                        "name": "jihoonson",
                        "key": "jihoonson",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?ownerId=jihoonson&avatarId=21898",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&ownerId=jihoonson&avatarId=21898",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&ownerId=jihoonson&avatarId=21898",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&ownerId=jihoonson&avatarId=21898"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Jihoon Son",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "America/Los_Angeles"
                    },
                    "body": "[~julienledem], thanks for creating this ticket.\n\nThe simplest solution is to add a surefire option -Darrow.vector.max_allocation_bytes=1048576 to limit the max allocation size. This will affect to all unit testings, but I think this is a valid solution because we can avoid the allocation of large memory for a vector which can cause OOM in poor test environments.\nAny thoughts on this solution?",
